intro: Stenanthemum notiale subsp. notiale, commonly known as the slender stenanthemum, is a flowering plant native to Western Australia. It belongs to the family Proteaceae and is characterized by its upright growth habit and narrow, linear leaves. The plant produces small, clustered white flowers that bloom during the winter months. It is typically found in sandy or gravelly soils in open habitats. Due to its limited distribution and specific habitat requirements, it is considered a rare and threatened species.
